Pepperidge Farm Dinner Rolls We value your trust in Pepperidge Farm, and promise your satisfaction. Pepperidge Farm products are crafted to make every day a special day. We hope you are as passionate about eating our products as we are about making them. Low fat. Cholesterol free.

Directions
Heating Instructions - For Conventional Oven/Toaster Oven: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Remove rolls from bag. Discard cardboard tray. Place rolls on a baking sheet, then place in oven and heat about 5 minutes. Gently pull rolls apart; wrap in a napkin. Serve immediately. For Microwave Oven: Remove rolls from bag. Discard cardboard tray. Loosely wrap rolls in paper towel. Microwave on High (100%) power 45 to 60 seconds. (Time given is for a full bag of rolls in a 600-watt microwave oven. Adjust timing as needed for your oven in 10-second intervals.) Gently pull rolls apart; wrap in a napkin. Serve immediately.

Serve piping hot in 6 to 8 minutes.

Directions
Easy as A - B - C.
A. Pre-heat oven to approximately 400 to 450 degrees F.
B. Remove from the bag the number of rolls to be baked and place separately on ungreased baking sheet or pan.
C. Brown to desired color (6 to 8 minutes), brush with melted butter before or after baking, and serve piping hot from the oven. Remove from bag before baking.

Storage
Unbaked Bunny Brown 'N Serve Rolls will stay fresh and ready for baking in this convenient bag for several days on your pantry shelf - For several weeks in your refrigerator - Indefinitely in your freezer - Ready for baking whenever you want fresh rolls.
